  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_07_xxxviii: For it is a thing very possible, that a man should be a very divine man, and ...",
  "body": "For it is a thing very possible, that a man should be a very divine man, and yet be altogether unknown. This thou must ever be mindful of, as of this also, that a man's true happiness doth consist in very few things. And that although thou dost despair, that thou shalt ever be a good either logician, or naturalist, yet thou art never the further off by it from being either liberal, or modest, or charitable, or obedient unto God.",
